ewspaper. “From his arrival at Villarreal, it was clear he was a special player. His speed and the ease of with which he went past his marker made him grow very fast in the team. “The team had found a special player, a great footballer. “The club worked quickly to improve his contract and increase his buy-out clause – from 65 million Euros to 100 million Euros. “But after making the young Nigerian one of the top earners on the team, things changed, he seemed to have lost that hunger, that speed and talent, which made him different.” Vanguard News Nigeria Super Eagles and Charleroi FC forward Victor Osimhen has stated that the football world is yet to see the best of his 2015 U-17 FIFA World Cup teammate Samuel Chukwueze who has been in flying form since being drafted to Spanish side Villarreal’s senior team few months ago. January 3, 2019 In "Sports" Villarreal of Spain winger, Samuel Chukwueze has disclosed that he is happy that his goal was enough to lift his team off bottom spot in La Liga. November 27, 2018 In "Sports" He was young enough to participate at this year's Under-20 World Cup, but Samuel Chukwueze is assuming a far greater role as a future Nigeria lynchpin with his country attempting to capture a fourth Africa Cup of Nations title. July 13, 2019 In "Sports"